item.title: This section should be removed
item.dc:creator: @CodeForFame CodeForFame
item.description:
@CodeForFame wrote:

[quote=“RSCShadow, post:36, topic:542838”][quote author=Jmood link=topic=661713.msg4425287#msg4425287 date=1400549229]

Well it is an old game. It’s hardly surprising that interest in developing stuff related to it will only decline.

Yea but at the same time you see other games replicated from the late 1990’s to early 2k and they have thousands of players. MoparClassic presents the perfect opportunity to stabilize this shitty community but yea… community driven project by a broken community ftw.

Keep blaming community, that will get the project going…
The people who started the project should be working on it no matter if they rest of the community decides to not work on it.

If its a community project than the community should also put effort into it. Expecting a couple people to do all the work isn’t right.
[/quote]You can’t just expect someone to launch an unfinished project, call it “community based” and assume that a bunch of people will contribute just because it’s open source. If you feel strongly about a project, work on it yourself and other people may or may not help out. Blaming “the community” isn’t going to get any more work done.[/quote]You obviously haven’t payed attention to the project at all… I alone have made over 30% of the commits to the project, and between me and 1 other person we have made over 80% of the commits. The next 3 highest commiters make up another 15%. 5 people making up 95% of the work is us doing exactly that.

Read full topic
